# ─── Dependencies ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# node_modules is NOT sent to the build context – installed in stage 1
# via `pnpm install`.  Keeping pnpm-lock.yaml is REQUIRED:
#   1. `--frozen-lockfile` in the Dockerfile requires it for reproducible builds.
#   2. CI/CD pipelines need it for deterministic dependency resolution.
node_modules
# pnpm-lock.yaml intentionally kept – see note above.

# ─── Next.js build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────
.next
out

# ─── Version control ─────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore

# ─── Development / editor files ───────────────────────────────────
*.md
*.log
.npmrc
.eslintrc*
.prettierrc*
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ─── Testing / CI ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
coverage
.nyc_output
Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml

# ─── OS clutter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
